The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems such as Max 2-CSP, Max Cut, and counting dominating sets, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of computer science related to data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper's focus on the design and analysis of algorithms suggests that it is more likely to belong to these sub-categories than to others such as computer vision or artificial intelligence.
